news.title: Pune: Cluster redevelopment of old wadas stuck in policy hurdles & opposition from residents
news.para: Pune's cluster development initiative, proposed eight years ago to redevelop old wadas and buildings, has seen minimal progress due to challenges in consolidating land and securing owner/tenant consent. Residents of aging housing societies face infrastructure issues, while policymakers struggle to accelerate reconstruction efforts.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt backs Noida authority's move to cancel 29 plots lying idle for two decades
news.para: Uttar Pradesh industrial development department has upheld Noida Authority's decision to cancel land allotments for 29 industrial units. The department dismissed a revision petition from Elevator IT Solutions Ltd, which challenged the cancellation for failing to commence construction despite repeated extensions and statutory relaxations.

news.title: Delhi may get ‘A+’ property zone as government reviews circle rates for Lutyens’ area, farmhouses
news.para: Delhi government is reviewing suggestions to revise circle rates, including a new 'A+' category for premium Lutyens' Delhi areas and an overhaul of farmhouse rates. Proposed biennial reviews and greater data transparency aim to align rates with market realities, boost revenue, and enhance investor confidence.

news.title: Orissa HC quashes inquiry report, restores PMAY-G benefits to eligible beneficiaries
news.para: The Orissa high court has overturned a government inquiry that disqualified several Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana–Gramin beneficiaries. The court found the inquiry flawed, violating established guidelines.  Beneficiaries, initially approved and receiving funds, were declared ineligible based on a late complaint. The court ordered the release of pending benefits, emphasizing the initial approval process.

news.title: Plots delayed, Allahabad HC asks YEIDA to pay penalty to 150 allottees
news.para: The Allahabad High Court upheld allottees' claims against YEIDA in a Rera appeal, ordering payment of pending dues with delay interest. The court rejected YEIDA's plea for refund of pre-deposited amounts, confirming their appropriation towards dues owed to buyers. This ruling protects homebuyers' rights and sets a precedent for timely compensation.

news.title: Bombay HC rejects builder’s plea against single judge hearing
news.para: The Bombay High Court dismissed a builder's objections, allowing a single judge to hear a green activist's petition concerning illegal construction in an open space. The court continued a stay on further development of the commercial building, which was allegedly built in a designated open space and within highway setback limits.

news.title: Nashik city registers 57% rise in properties over past 10 years
news.para: Nashik's property market has surged by 57% in a decade, adding 2.2 lakh new units to reach 6 lakh properties. This rapid expansion is driven by increased demand for housing and commercial spaces, fueled by job opportunities, investment potential, and migration from surrounding districts.

news.title: Seven years on, redevelopment begins at four Bengaluru development body complexes
news.para: Seven years after the initial tender, the Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) has commenced redevelopment of four of its seven ageing commercial complexes under a public-private partnership. This initiative aims to transform loss-making public assets into modern commercial hubs, with work already underway at Indiranagar, RT Nagar, Sadashivanagar, and Vijayanagar complexes.

news.title: Karnataka government sets rules for layout approvals on converted land outside planning areas
news.para: In a significant move, Karnataka's Rural Development Department has unveiled a set of regulations aimed at streamlining building layout approvals on converted lands within the Gram Panchayat jurisdiction. Developers are now required to secure design approvals before obtaining their property identification numbers.

news.title: FPCE wants changes in RERA law, pitches for rules to verify promoters' track record
news.para: A homebuyers' association is urging the government to amend the RERA law. They want builders' past performance to be checked before new projects are approved. The association also seeks compensation for buyers if promised facilities are not delivered. A uniform refund policy for cancellations is also demanded. These changes aim to protect consumers from errant developers.

news.title: Rajasthan: RIICO eases land use norms, likely to suffer revenue losses due to lower rates
news.para: RIICO has reformed land use norms in Rajasthan, allowing industrial plots to be converted to commercial, residential, institutional, and mixed-use categories. New charges are introduced for these conversions, with rates varying based on the new land use.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh expedites process of establishing IT cluster park in 10 acre plot in Kadapa
news.para: Andhra Pradesh is accelerating its IT development by establishing a new IT cluster park in Kadapa, alongside Visakhapatnam's AI hub.  This move is part of a decentralized growth strategy, aiming to foster tech ecosystems across the state.  The government has allocated land and funds for infrastructure, encouraging IT firms and startups to invest in the region.

news.title: Kolkata: Sector V likely to pay property tax via UAA from next financial year
news.para: NDITA has submitted its final proposal to the state for implementing the unit area assessment (UAA) system for property tax collection in Sector V. This new system aims to streamline tax assessment and collection, allowing establishments to self-assess and pay taxes. The UAA system is expected to be introduced from the next financial year.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh: STF arrests man for duping real estate firm of over ₹6 crore
news.para: UP Special Task Force apprehended Neeraj Kumar Jaiswal, wanted for defrauding a real estate firm of Rs 6.40 crore. Jaiswal, an ex-agent, allegedly forged documents with an accomplice to embezzle funds. After returning a portion, he fled to Nepal when questioned. He faces multiple criminal charges and has been handed over to local police.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM inspects Noida International Airport
news.para: Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath reviewed the underconstruction Noida International Airport in Jewar. Officials assured him that all pending work will be completed by November 15. The airport is set to become a symbol of UP's development. Connectivity and passenger amenities are key focus areas. This airport will make UP the first state in India with five international airports.

news.title: Goa: Affordable housing for gaonkars on 20% build-up comunidade land
news.para: New rules allow Comunidades to develop land with developers, reserving 20% for affordable housing for gaonkars. Developers must submit detailed proposals, commence work within three months of permissions, and face project inspection by the Comunidade. Developers can appeal refusals, but must vacate if appeals fail.

news.title: Rajasthan RERA extends QPR submission deadline due to technical glitches in new online system
news.para: Rajasthan RERA has extended the deadline for developers to submit their Quarterly Progress Reports. The new deadline is November 30, a month later than the original October 31 date. This extension is due to technical problems with the recently upgraded online platform. No penalties will be charged for submissions made within the extended period.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to make use of unused CHB land to ease housing problem
news.para: Chandigarh's Chief Secretary H Rajesh Prasad announced plans to fully utilize vacant land for housing, adhering to the Master Plan and Supreme Court heritage rulings. He also directed efforts to establish a skill university, resolve service cases, and implement UGC regulations, emphasizing quality education and industry linkages for student development.

news.title: Illegal commercial complex on residential plot demolished in Meerut
news.para: In a significant move to enforce urban regulations, the Uttar Pradesh Housing Development Board has leveled an unauthorized commercial complex in Meerut's Shastri Nagar. This operation, executed on Saturday, complies with a directive from the Supreme Court issued in December 2024, calling for stringent observance of urban planning norms.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh: ₹3 crore under PMAY 2.0 approved for Una, to benefit 117 families
news.para: In Una district, Himachal Pradesh, a noteworthy initiative under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana Urban 2.0 will benefit 117 families, each receiving a financial boost of Rs 2.5 lakh. The scheme, with a total allocation of Rs 3 crore, encourages families to initiate their construction projects without delay, aiming for completion within a year.
